From d7eee43e587054d46f6f4cdb199558ad091a20a8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: operations-jacrentals <operations@jacrentals.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 22:49:01 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] Make Void and Send-to-Collections reachable again (C1,
 C2)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Both actions were fully built — manager-tier gate, reason-code confirm
popup, collections overlay, auto-blacklist, audit-log entry, and live
js-void-invoice / js-col-queue / js-col-recall handlers — but their ONLY
trigger markup lived in DETAIL.invoices, and the standalone Invoices card is
retired (config.js COLUMNS/COLUMN_OF carry no 'invoices' member). So the tail
of the AR chain was unclickable: a late invoice could be paid, printed or
refunded, but never voided and never sent to the agency. The only visible
alternative was raw Blacklist, which skips the whole record-keeping path — no
agency placement, no amount placed, no reason code.

Ported the conditions verbatim into invoiceStatMenu, the menu that DOES
render on the customer's embedded invoice list:
  Void            canMoney() && invoiceVoidable(i)
  (else)          "Refund to void" hint when a payment is assigned
  Recall          manager tier && invoiceCollectionsActive(i)
  Wrangle         manager tier && status in Late/Late+30/60/90/Collections
                  && balance > 0.005 && !locked && !refunded
Same js- hooks, same data-rec, same gates — render surface only, no new
logic. Handlers re-check their own tier, so the gate is defence-in-depth.
Items use the menu's existing im-item/im-sep pattern, so no new component,
no new data-r and no WINDOW_CATALOG entry.

VERIFIED end to end in the browser on the #local seed, through the real UI —
opened customer C0033, expanded invoice 02i07Ju26 (status Late, $897.08
owed, $0 paid, voidable, not in collections) and opened its status menu:
  before:  $ Pay · Print · Send(disabled)
  after:   $ Pay · Print · Send(disabled) · ⊘ Void invoice · ⚑ Wrangle to Collections
with js-void-invoice and js-col-queue present on the new items.

NOTE for whoever verifies next: the first run showed NO change because the
browser was still running app.js?v=<old token> — index.html is cached too, so
a plain reload is not enough. Bump the token (or load the page with a
cache-busting query) before trusting a visual check. That is exactly the
failure ci/check-cachebust.mjs exists to prevent. The bump used for this
verification was reverted; /deploy owns the real one.

Gates: smoke, logic-test, lease-test, lease-deploy-test, promote-test,
deck-test, cachebust-test, gen-rule-usage --check, check-window-catalog,
check-design-md, gen-code-map --check — all green.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
